descript.abstract: This layer is based on known slide events from City records including those in the right of ways and private property. It has not been updated since its creation circa. 1995. The areas identified were table digitized from a wall size dot map which was subsequently superimposed on larger 200 scale maps from which they were digitized.
descript.purpose: To implement and regulate the City of Seattle's Environmentally Critical Areas policies.

overview.eaover: Three new fields were added 11/9/2011 to reference slide case files held by SPU and DPD geotechnical engineering sections. FOLIO_ID text 40 : represents the ID to slide files from DPD and SPU filing IDs EVENT_ADDR text 254 : event address FIELD_INSP_BY text 30 : field inspected by DPD staff initials and/or City department
